The `strlen()` function in C is used to find the length of a string (i.e., the number of characters in it, excluding the null terminator `'\0'`).\
It is defined in the `` library and returns the length as a `size_t` which gives the result as a non-negative integer.

---

**Example:**

```c
#include
#include

int main() {
    // Declare and initialize a string message
    char message[] = "Hello";

    // Use strlen() to calculate the number of characters in the message
    int length = strlen(message);

    // Print the length of the message
    printf("Length of the message: %d\n", length);  // Output: 5

    return 0;
}
```

